20 minutes later, you'd be looking to tell somebody.

63
00:03:27,270 --> 00:03:28,770
而你第一个想要分享的对象
And the first one you gonna want to tell,

64
00:03:28,770 --> 00:03:30,800
想要吹嘘的对象就是我
that you gonna want to brag to is going to be me.

65
00:03:30,810 --> 00:03:33,270
我不会这样做
Oh, I ain't saying that.

66
00:03:33,270 --> 00:03:35,570
我看到你在偷看她
I see where you be eyeing her.

67
00:03:35,580 --> 00:03:37,840
我所有女人都看，我不会错过任何女人
I eye all the women. I don't miss nothing.

68
00:03:37,850 --> 00:03:39,150
别听别人说…
Don't never let nobody tell you

69
00:03:39,380 --> 00:03:40,180
特洛伊·马克森不看女人
Troy Maxson don't eye the women.

70
00:03:40,310 --> 00:03:41,650
你顗觎她呢
Hey, you been doing more than eyeing her.

71
00:03:41,720 --> 00:03:42,920
你请她喝酒了
You done bought her a drink or two.

72
00:03:42,950 --> 00:03:44,250
天啊，我是请过她，那又如何？
Hell, yeah, I bought her a drink. What that mean?

73
00:03:44,250 --> 00:03:45,620
我也请过你喝酒
I bought you one, too.

74
00:03:45,620 --> 00:03:47,250
那算什么，就因为我请她喝了一杯？
What that mean, 'cause I buy her a drink?

75
00:03:47,260 --> 00:03:48,550
我只是出于礼貌
I'm just being polite.

76
00:03:48,560 --> 00:03:49,760
你请她喝一杯完全可以
It's all right to buy her one drink.

77
00:03:49,760 --> 00:03:51,620
那就是出于礼貌
That's what you call being polite.

78
00:03:51,630 --> 00:03:53,290
但当你继续请她喝酒
But when you want to be buying two or three,

79
00:03:53,290 --> 00:03:54,830
那就是顗觎
that's what you call eyeing her.

80
00:03:54,830 --> 00:03:56,660
听着，你认识我这样久了
Look here. As long as you've known me,

81
00:03:56,660 --> 00:03:58,630
你有听过我去追求女人吗？
you ever known me to chase after women?

82
00:03:58,630 --> 00:04:00,870
当然有，一直认识你以来你都有
Hell, yeah! Long as I've known you.

83
00:04:00,870 --> 00:04:02,300
你忘了我认识你多久了
You're forgetting, I knew you when.

84
00:04:02,300 --> 00:04:04,570
我在说在我跟罗斯结婚后
I'm talking about since I been married to Rose.

85
00:04:04,570 --> 00:04:06,740
噢…那倒没有
Oh... not since you been married to Rose.

86
00:04:06,740 --> 00:04:08,270
我可以说，那倒是真的
That's the truth, though. I can say that.

87
00:04:08,280 --> 00:04:09,910
明白了吧，没什么可说
All right then. Case closed.

88
00:04:10,610 --> 00:04:13,280
我在艾伯塔的房子外看见过你
I see you be walking up around Alberta's house.

89
00:04:13,280 --> 00:04:14,750
那种时候你应该在泰勒的酒吧才对
You supposed to be at Taylors',

90
00:04:14,750 --> 00:04:16,050
而你却在那里出现了
and you be walking up around there.

91
00:04:16,050 --> 00:04:17,320
你为何在意我去哪？
What you watching where I'm walking for?

92
00:04:17,390 --> 00:04:18,490
我也没在意你去哪
I don't be watching after you.

93
00:04:18,520 --> 00:04:20,650
不，我看见你在那里不只一次
No, I seen you walking around there more than once.

94
00:04:20,730 --> 00:04:22,130
当然，我们经常在一起
Hell, you liable to see me walking anywhere.

95
00:04:22,160 --> 00:04:23,990
你看到我在那里不代表什么
That don't mean nothing 'cause you seen me walking around there.

96
00:04:23,990 --> 00:04:25,320
她从哪来的？
Where'd she come from, anyway?

97
00:04:25,330 --> 00:04:26,760
她就好像突然出现一样
She just kinda showed up one day.

98
00:04:26,760 --> 00:04:28,060
塔拉哈西，你看到她
Tallahassee. You can look at that

99
00:04:28,060 --> 00:04:30,030
就知道她是来自佛罗里达州[塔拉哈西是其首府]
and tell she one of them Florida gals.

100
00:04:30,030 --> 00:04:32,570
那里的女人都亭亭玉立
They got some big, healthy women down there.

101
00:04:32,570 --> 00:04:34,300
就像树一样高大
Grow them right up out of the ground.

102
00:04:34,300 --> 00:04:35,940
她有印度人的血统
She got a little bit of Indian in her.

103
00:04:35,940 --> 00:04:37,900
很多在佛罗里达州的黑人都有印度人血统
Most of them niggers in Florida got some Indian in them.

104
00:04:37,910 --> 00:04:39,970
我不知道她是不是混血儿
Yeah, I don't know about that Indian part,

105
00:04:39,970 --> 00:04:43,010
但她真的很高大
but she damn sure big and healthy.

106
00:04:43,010 --> 00:04:45,080
要是让她穿上长袜
Woman wears some big stockings.

107
00:04:45,080 --> 00:04:49,620
再张开她那双诱人的腿，真棒
Got them crazy big legs, and hips wide as the Mississippi river.

108
00:04:49,620 --> 00:04:50,950
双腿并不重要
Legs don't mean nothing.

109
00:04:50,950 --> 00:04:52,790
它们只会在做爱时阻碍你
You don't do nothing but push 'em out of the way.

110
00:04:52,790 --> 00:04:54,350
但是臀部可重要了
But them hips,

111
00:04:54,360 --> 00:04:55,790
它们坐在你上面时软呼呼的
they cushion the ride.

112
00:04:55,790 --> 00:04:57,590
特洛伊，不能这样算
Troy, you ain't got no sense!

113
00:04:57,590 --> 00:05:00,660
那是真的，像你年轻做爱时一样
It's the truth. Like you riding on goodyears!

114
00:05:03,660 --> 00:05:05,700
你们在这里都在聊什么了？
What you all out here getting into?

115
00:05:05,700 --> 00:05:07,930
女人，你为何在意我们在聊什么？
What you worried about what we getting into for, woman?

116
00:05:08,010 --> 00:05:09,010
这是男人之间的讨论
This is men talk.

117
00:05:09,040 --> 00:05:10,640
我又怎么会在意呢？
What I care what you all are talking about?

118
00:05:10,640 --> 00:05:11,940
博诺，你要留下来吃晚餐吗？
Bono, you gonna stay for supper?

119
00:05:11,940 --> 00:05:13,340
不了，谢谢，罗斯
No, thank you, Rose,

120
00:05:13,340 --> 00:05:15,770
露西尔说她今晚要煮猪脚
but Lucille say she cooking up a pot of pigfeet.

121
00:05:15,780 --> 00:05:17,840
猪脚？那我也跟你回去了
Pigfeet? Hell, I'm going home with you.

122
00:05:17,850 --> 00:05:20,110
要是你家煮猪脚，我甚至会在你那睡一晚
I might even stay the night, you got some pigfeet.

123
00:05:20,110 --> 00:05:22,050
罗斯，你里面有煮什么比猪脚还棒的吗？
You got something in there to top them pigfeet, Rose?

124
00:05:22,050 --> 00:05:24,620
我在煮鸡肉，今晚吃鸡肉和羽衣甘蓝叶
I'm cooking up some chicken. I got some chicken and collard greens.

125
00:05:24,620 --> 00:05:25,820
那你先进去继续烹调
Well, you go on back in the house.

126
00:05:25,820 --> 00:05:27,050
让博诺和我继续刚才的话题
Let me and Bono finish what we talking about.

127
00:05:27,050 --> 00:05:29,920
这是男人之间的讨论，我待会也有些事要跟你讨论
This is men talk. I got some talk for you later.

128
00:05:29,920 --> 00:05:31,960
你也知道我要说什么的
And you know what kind of talk I mean, too.

129
00:05:31,960 --> 00:05:33,690
你先进去准备下[指做爱]
You go on in there and powder it up.

130
00:05:33,690 --> 00:05:34,990
特洛伊，够了！
Troy, stop it!

131
00:05:35,000 --> 00:05:38,030
噢，来吧，女人
Oh, woman, come here.

132
00:05:38,030 --> 00:05:41,400
博诺，听着
Oh! Look here, Bono.

133
00:05:41,400 --> 00:05:43,940
我第一次看到这女人时
When I first met this woman,

134
00:05:43,940 --> 00:05:45,840
我就行动了
I got out that place there.

135
00:05:45,940 --> 00:05:48,840
我准备好我的马匹
Hitch up my pony, saddle up my mare

136
00:05:48,940 --> 00:05:51,640
因为那里有个女人在等着我
there's a woman out there for me somewhere

137
00:05:51,710 --> 00:05:53,380
我到处找寻她的踪影
I looked at here, looked at there,

138
00:05:53,380 --> 00:05:55,710
然后看到罗斯时我就彻底被她迷住了
saw Rose, and I latched on to her.

139
00:05:55,720 --> 00:05:57,680
我想也没想就上前跟她说…
I latched on to her and I told her...

140
00:05:57,690 --> 00:05:59,050
我来告诉你当时到底发生了什么事
Now, I'm gonna tell you the truth.

141
00:05:59,050 --> 00:06:03,720
我跟她说：宝贝，我不想要结婚
I latched on to her and told her, "baby, I don't want to marry.

142
00:06:03,720 --> 00:06:05,190
我只想成为你的男人
"I just want to be your man."

143
00:06:05,190 --> 00:06:07,890
罗斯回答我…你来告诉他，罗
Rose told me... Tell him what you told me, Ro.

144
00:06:07,900 --> 00:06:09,860
我跟他说如果他不打算长相厮守
I told him if he wasn't the marrying kind,

145
00:06:09,860 --> 00:06:12,030
那就滚开，别挡着那些想的人前来
then move out of the way, so the marrying kind could find me.

146
00:06:12,030 --> 00:06:14,730
她真这么说了：朋友，你在挡着我
That's what she told me, "nigger, you in my way.

147
00:06:14,740 --> 00:06:16,000
你在阻挡我的视线
"You blocking the view.

148
00:06:16,000 --> 00:06:18,000
滚开，让我找我的爱人
"Move out the way, so I can find me a husband."

149
00:06:18,010 --> 00:06:20,740
- 我想了几天  - 你才没有
- I thought it over 2-3 days.  - Two-three days, nothing.

150
00:06:20,740 --> 00:06:22,070
你那晚就回来了
You was back the same night.

151
00:06:22,080 --> 00:06:24,410
我回来并跟她说：好吧，宝贝
I come back, told her, "okay, baby,

152
00:06:24,410 --> 00:06:26,150
但我要买一只矮脚公鸡[比正常公鸡小，但好斗]
"but I'm gonna buy me a banty rooster

153
00:06:26,150 --> 00:06:27,980
把它放在后院里
"and put him out there in the backyard.

154
00:06:27,980 --> 00:06:29,690
当它看到陌生人
"And when he see a stranger come,

155
00:06:29,720 --> 00:06:31,420
它就会到处跑跟大声啼叫
"he gonna flap his wings and crow."

156
00:06:31,450 --> 00:06:33,290
博诺，看这里，我看着前门就够烦了
Look here, Bono. I done watched that front door by myself.

157
00:06:33,290 --> 00:06:35,990
我担心的是[她的]后庭
It was that back door I was worried about.

158
00:06:35,990 --> 00:06:38,820
特洛伊，别说了，你在撒谎
Don't talk like that! Troy, you're not but telling a lie.

159
00:06:38,830 --> 00:06:40,190
但是我们结婚后才发现
Only thing was, we first got married,

160
00:06:40,190 --> 00:06:42,930
忘了那公鸡吧，因为我们根本负担不起后院
forget the rooster. We ain't had no yard.

161
00:06:43,000 --> 00:06:44,000
我也明白
I hear you tell it.

162
00:06:44,030 --> 00:06:46,770
露西尔和我以前住在洛根街[美国，丹佛]
Me and Lucille was staying down there on Logan street.

163
00:06:46,770 --> 00:06:49,100
我们有两间房子，还有个厕所在后院里
Had two rooms with the outhouse in the back.

164
00:06:49,100 --> 00:06:50,900
我平常都不介意的
I ain't mind the outhouse none.

165
00:06:50,910 --> 00:06:53,440
但当冬天时有阵该死的冷锋吹过
But when that goddamn wind blew through there in the winter,

166
00:06:53,440 --> 00:06:55,170
我就恨死它了！[以前家里没有水管]
that's what I'm talking about!

167
00:06:55,480 --> 00:06:56,940
直至今天，我还在想
To this day, I wonder why the hell

168
00:06:56,940 --> 00:06:59,450
为何我会住在那里六年之久
I ever stayed down there for six long years.

169
00:06:59,450 --> 00:07:02,010
我当时也不知道可以怎办
But, see, I didn't know I could do no better.

170
00:07:02,020 --> 00:07:04,880
我以为只有白人才配有室内厕所什么的
I thought only white folks had inside toilets and things.

171
00:07:04,960 --> 00:07:06,060
很多人也像这样
A lot of folks don't think

172
00:07:06,090 --> 00:07:07,820
安于现状
they can do no better than they're doing now.

173
00:07:07,820 --> 00:07:09,020
那是些要改变的想法
Just something you gotta learn.

174
00:07:09,020 --> 00:07:10,960
就像很多人还去贝拉的店买东西
A lot of folks still shop at Bella's.

175
00:07:10,960 --> 00:07:12,760
贝拉卖的东西没问题啊，她卖的食物也很新鲜
Ain't nothing wrong with Bella's. She got fresh food.

176
00:07:12,760 --> 00:07:14,490
我不是在说她卖的食物有没有问题
I ain't said nothing about if she got fresh food.

177
00:07:14,500 --> 00:07:15,960
我在说她卖的价钱
I'm talking about what she charge.

178
00:07:15,960 --> 00:07:17,930
同样的货品她比A&P卖贵十美分
She charges 10 cents more than the A&P.

179
00:07:17,930 --> 00:07:19,500
A&P没为我做过什么
A&P ain't never done nothing for me.

180
00:07:19,500 --> 00:07:21,470
我会选择消费在我认为对的地方
I spend my money where I'm treated right.

181
00:07:21,540 --> 00:07:22,740
我到贝拉的店里说
I go down to Bella, say,

182
00:07:22,770 --> 00:07:25,240
我要买一条面包，星期五付钱，她就给我了
"i need a loaf of bread, I'll pay you Friday," she gives it to me.

183
00:07:25,240 --> 00:07:27,210
如果我还在
What sense that make when I got money

184
00:07:27,210 --> 00:07:28,810
其他地方消费
to spend it somewhere else

185
00:07:28,810 --> 00:07:30,240
把这个卖人情给我的人忘掉，我还算什么？
and ignore the person who done right by me?

186
00:07:30,240 --> 00:07:31,450
圣经里没教人忘恩负义
That ain't in the Bible.

187
00:07:31,450 --> 00:07:33,180
我们不是在谈论圣经
We ain't talking about what's in the Bible.

188
00:07:33,280 --> 00:07:35,080
明知道她卖贵了，还在那买东西，这样理智吗？
What sense it make to shop there when she overcharges?

189
00:07:35,080 --> 00:07:36,920
那你去你想去的地方买
Well, you do your shopping where you want to,

190
00:07:36,950 --> 00:07:38,790
我去卖过人情给我的地方买
I do my shopping where people been good to me.

191
00:07:38,820 --> 00:07:40,250
噢，我只是不认同她卖贵了而已
Oh, I don't think it's right for her to overcharge, that's all.

192
00:07:40,250 --> 00:07:41,790
听着，我该走了
Look here, I got to be getting on.

193
00:07:41,790 --> 00:07:43,120
露西尔都要发怒了
Lucille gonna be raising all kind of hell.

194
00:07:43,120 --> 00:07:44,890
朋友，你要去哪，我们还没喝完这瓶呢
Where you going, nigger? We ain't finished this pint.

195
00:07:44,960 --> 00:07:46,160
先喝完吧
Come here finish this pint.

196
00:07:46,190 --> 00:07:50,060
我会留下啊，如果你请我喝的话
Well, hell, I am, if you ever turn the bottle loose.

197
00:07:50,060 --> 00:07:52,030
我唯一要感谢A&P的地方
Only thing I'll say about the A&P is,

198
00:07:52,030 --> 00:07:54,330
就是他们让科丽在那工作
I'm glad Cory got that job down there.

199
00:07:54,830 --> 00:07:56,830
帮补一下他的开支
Help him with his school clothes and things.

200
00:07:56,840 --> 00:07:58,870
加布搬走了，我们有点捉襟见肘
Gabe done moved out, things getting tight around here.

201
00:07:58,870 --> 00:08:00,110
他有份工作
He got that job,

202
00:08:00,110 --> 00:08:01,840
至少可以照顾下自己
he can start to look out for himself.

203
00:08:01,840 --> 00:08:05,080
科丽被一间大学的美式足球队录取了
Cory done got recruited by a college football team.

204
00:08:05,080 --> 00:08:08,210
我跟他说过大学的美式足球队到底是怎么一回事
I told that boy about that college football stuff.

205
00:08:08,220 --> 00:08:11,120
那些白人不会让他碰美式足球的
The white man ain't gonna let him get nowhere with that football.

206
00:08:11,120 --> 00:08:13,190
他第一次来我就跟他解释过了
I told him when he first come to me with it.

207
00:08:13,190 --> 00:08:15,990
现在你告诉我他更着迷了
Now, you come telling me he done got more tied up in it.

208
00:08:15,990 --> 00:08:18,090
他该去车行工作
He ought to get recruited in how to fix cars,

209
00:08:18,160 --> 00:08:19,760
还是做点能令他过活的事
or some way he can make a living.

210
00:08:19,790 --> 00:08:21,960
他不是想成为职业美式足球员
He ain't talking about making no living playing football.

211
00:08:21,960 --> 00:08:24,000
那只是他的兴趣而已
It's just something the boys in school do.

212
00:08:24,000 --> 00:08:25,520
他们会派负责人员来
They're gonna send a recruiter by

213
00:08:25,550 --> 00:08:27,070
跟你商讨，他会跟你说
to talk to you. He'll tell you.

214
00:08:27,100 --> 00:08:28,200
他不是想成为职业美式足球员
He ain't talking about making no living playing football.

215
00:08:28,200 --> 00:08:29,940
被录取是个荣誉
It's an honor to be recruited.

216
00:08:29,940 --> 00:08:32,300
他不会走得远的，博诺就懂
It ain't gonna get him nowhere, Bono'll tell you that.

217
00:08:32,570 --> 00:08:35,870
如果他跟你一样那么有运动细胞，他会成为伟大的球员
If he be like you in sports, he gonna be all right.

218
00:08:35,880 --> 00:08:38,240
这么久以来只有两个人打棒球比你好
Ain't but two men ever played baseball good as you.

219
00:08:38,250 --> 00:08:40,310
就是贝比·鲁斯和乔什·吉普森[皆为著名棒球员]
That's Babe Ruth and Josh Gibson.

220
00:08:40,310 --> 00:08:42,850
他们就是唯一比你有更多全垒打的人
Them the only two men ever hit more home runs than you.

221
00:08:42,850 --> 00:08:45,080
打棒球给了我什么？我没有地方上厕所
And what it ever get me? I ain't got a pot to piss in,

222
00:08:45,160 --> 00:08:46,360
又或者靠此买过一间房子
or a window to throw it out of.

223
00:08:46,390 --> 00:08:48,220
时代不同了，特洛伊
Times have changed since you were playing baseball, Troy.

224
00:08:48,220 --> 00:08:50,290
你打棒球都是战争之前了，很多事情都改变了
That was before the war. Times have changed a lot since then.

225
00:08:50,290 --> 00:08:51,560
有什么改变了？
How the hell they done changed?

226
00:08:51,560 --> 00:08:53,160
现在很多有色人种都在球队里
They got a lot of colored boys playing ball now.

227
00:08:53,160 --> 00:08:54,590
棒球也好，美式足球也好
Baseball and football.

228
00:08:54,600 --> 00:08:57,900
罗，你说对了，时代不同了，特洛伊
You right about that, Ro. Times have changed, Troy.

229
00:08:57,970 --> 00:08:59,270
你只是生不逢时而已
You just come along too early.

230
00:08:59,300 --> 00:09:03,000
世上没有所谓“生不逢时”
There ought not never have been no time called "too early."

231
00:09:04,300 --> 00:09:06,840
以他为例…
Now you take that fellow...

232
00:09:06,840 --> 00:09:08,370
那个以前在洋基队
What's that fellow they had playing

233
00:09:08,380 --> 00:09:09,640
当右外野手的叫什么？
right field back then for the Yankees?

234
00:09:09,640 --> 00:09:10,580
博诺，你该记得的
You remember who I'm talking about, Bono,

235
00:09:10,610 --> 00:09:11,930
在洋基队当右外野手的那个
played right field for the Yankees.

236
00:09:11,960 --> 00:09:13,310
- 塞尔柯克？ - 对，就是他
- Selkirk?  - Yeah, Selkirk, that's it!

237
00:09:13,310 --> 00:09:16,920
他的职业生涯打击率是点二六九，你看得出了吗？
Man's batting 269, you understand? 269!

238
00:09:16,920 --> 00:09:20,590
那合理吗？我的打击率是点四三二，有三十七个是全垒打
What sense that make? I'm batting 432 with 37 home runs!

239
00:09:20,590 --> 00:09:23,860
他的打击率才点二六九，却在洋基队里当右外野手！
He's batting 269, playing right field for the Yankees!

240
00:09:23,860 --> 00:09:25,990
我昨天看到乔什·吉普森的女儿
I saw Josh Gibson's daughter yesterday.

241
00:09:25,990 --> 00:09:28,630
她穿着破烂的鞋到处跑
She's running around with raggedy shoes on her feet.

242
00:09:28,630 --> 00:09:30,230
我敢打赌塞尔柯克的女儿
I bet you Selkirk's daughter ain't running around

243
00:09:30,230 --> 00:09:32,160
可不是穿着什么破烂的到处走
with no raggedy shoes on her feet. I bet you that.

244
00:09:32,170 --> 00:09:34,100
现在很多职业棒球员都是有色人种了
They got a lot of colored baseball players now.

245
00:09:34,100 --> 00:09:35,240
杰基·罗宾森是第一个
Jackie Robinson was the first.

246
00:09:35,240 --> 00:09:37,270
杰基·罗宾森都是名星了
Folks had to wait for Jackie Robinson.

247
00:09:37,270 --> 00:09:40,170
我看过无数比杰基·罗宾森还会打棒球的黑人
I done seen 100 niggers play baseball better than Jackie Robinson.

248
00:09:40,170 --> 00:09:43,180
我甚至看过杰基·罗宾森都进不了的球队
Hell, I seen some teams Jackie Robinson couldn't even make!

249
00:09:43,180 --> 00:09:44,410
还说什么杰基·罗宾森？
What you talking about, Jackie Robinson?

250
00:09:44,410 --> 00:09:46,250
杰基·罗宾森只是个无名小卒而已！
Jackie Robinson wasn't nobody!

251
00:09:46,250 --> 00:09:47,910
我要说的是如果你会打球
I'm talking about if you could play ball,

252
00:09:47,920 --> 00:09:49,180
他们就该给你机会
then they ought to let you play.

253
00:09:49,180 --> 00:09:50,350
而不是在意你的肤色人种
Don't matter what color you are.

254
00:09:50,350 --> 00:09:52,180
还说我生不逢时
Come telling me I come along too early.

255
00:09:52,190 --> 00:09:55,390
如果你会打球，他们就该给你机会
If you can play, then they ought to let you play.

256
00:09:55,390 --> 00:09:57,020
你再继续这么喝会死的
You gonna drink yourself to death.

257
00:09:57,020 --> 00:09:59,060
不用喝那么多吧
You don't need to be drinking like that.

258
00:09:59,060 --> 00:10:02,290
噢，死神而已，我都见过了
Oh! Death ain't nothing. I done seen him,

259
00:10:02,300 --> 00:10:04,330
还跟他搏斗过，不用你来跟我说
I done wrestled with him. You can't tell me nothing about death.

260
00:10:04,330 --> 00:10:07,930
死神不过是个外角的快速球
Death ain't nothing but a fastball on the outside corner,

261
00:10:07,940 --> 00:10:09,900
而你知道我有什么能耐
and you know what I do with that.

262
00:10:09,900 --> 00:10:11,670
博诺，看这里，我有在说谎吗？
Look here, Bono, am I lying?

263
00:10:11,670 --> 00:10:14,640
你扔个到腰水平高度的快速球
You get one of them fastballs about waist high

264
00:10:14,640 --> 00:10:16,240
从外角扔过来
on the outside corner of the plate

265
00:10:16,240 --> 00:10:18,110
那简直易如反掌
where you can get the meat of the bat on it,

266
00:10:18,110 --> 00:10:21,350
老天啊，我会把它打到出场外
and, good god, you could kiss it good-bye.

267
00:10:21,350 --> 00:10:23,420
- 我在吹嘘吗？ - 不，你在说事实
- Am I lying?  - No, you telling the truth.

268
00:10:23,490 --> 00:10:24,590
我亲眼看见过
I seen you do it.

269
00:10:24,620 --> 00:10:28,090
如果我在吹牛，那会是天大的谎话
If I'm lying, that's 450 feet worth of lying.

270
00:10:28,120 --> 00:10:30,260
死神来我来说就是这么回事
That's all death is to me.

271
00:10:30,260 --> 00:10:32,930
一个从外角扔来的快速球
A fastball on the outside corner.

272
00:10:32,930 --> 00:10:35,190
我不知道你为何说起死亡了？
I don't know why you want to get on talking about death?

273
00:10:35,200 --> 00:10:36,430
说说又没有问题
Ain't nothing wrong with talking about death.

274
00:10:36,430 --> 00:10:38,330
那是生命的一部分啊，每个人都必经
That's a part of life! Everybody gonna die.

275
00:10:38,330 --> 00:10:39,930
你会死，我会死
You gonna die. I'm gonna die.

276
00:10:39,930 --> 00:10:41,670
博诺会死，天啊，所有人都会死
Bono gonna die. Hell, we all gonna die.

277
00:10:41,670 --> 00:10:43,000
但你也没必要继续说吧
But you ain't got to talk about it.

278
00:10:43,000 --> 00:10:44,140
我不喜欢说这种事
I don't like talking about it.

279
00:10:44,140 --> 00:10:45,300
那是你提起的
Well, you the one brought it up.

280
00:10:45,310 --> 00:10:47,110
博诺和我刚才在说棒球
Me and Bono talking about baseball.

281
00:10:47,110 --> 00:10:49,140
你突然说我会喝死
You come telling me I'm gonna drink myself to death.

282
00:10:49,210 --> 00:10:50,110
不是吗，博诺？
Ain't that right, Bono?

283
00:10:50,140 --> 00:10:52,710
你知道我一周只有一晚去喝酒
Now you know I drink just but one night out the week,

284
00:10:52,780 --> 00:10:53,680
那是星期五晚
that's Friday night.

285
00:10:53,710 --> 00:10:55,950
我不会喝多
I drink just enough to where I can handle it.

286
00:10:56,020 --> 00:10:56,920
然后我就会离开，不碰它了
Then I leaves it alone. I cuts it loose.

287
00:10:56,950 --> 00:10:59,420
所以你不必担心我会喝死
So, you ain't got to worry about me drinking myself to death

288
00:10:59,420 --> 00:11:01,190
因为我不害怕死亡
'cause I ain't worrying about death.

289
00:11:01,190 --> 00:11:04,020
我见过他，跟他搏斗过
I done seen him, done wrestled with him.

290
00:11:04,090 --> 00:11:05,190
跟你说，博诺
Look here, Bono.

291
00:11:05,220 --> 00:11:08,430
我有天看到死神举军冲向我
I look up one day, and death is marching straight at me,

292
00:11:08,430 --> 00:11:10,700
像是阅兵时的士军队一样
like soldiers on parade.

293
00:11:10,700 --> 00:11:13,200
当时死神大军在冲向我
The army of death was marching straight at me.

294
00:11:13,200 --> 00:11:16,470
当时是一九四一年七月中
It was the middle of July, 1941.

295
00:11:16,470 --> 00:11:19,040
然而却像冬天一般冷
And it got real cold, just like it be winter.

296
00:11:19,040 --> 00:11:20,470
那时候死神他啊
And it seemed like death, himself,

297
00:11:20,470 --> 00:11:22,710
好像举手碰了我肩膀一下
reached out and touched me on the shoulder.

298
00:11:22,710 --> 00:11:26,180
他像我现在碰你一样，我感受到那寒意
He touched me like I touch you now. I got cold as ice.

299
00:11:26,180 --> 00:11:27,380
死神就站在那里，对我露出不友善的笑容
Death standing there, grinning at me.

300
00:11:27,380 --> 00:11:29,250
特洛伊，别说了
Troy, why don't you hush that talk.

301
00:11:29,250 --> 00:11:32,480
我说：死神先生，你想要什么？要带走我吗？
I said, "what you want, Mr. death? You be wanting me?

302
00:11:32,490 --> 00:11:34,450
你不再派你的小卒来了吗？
"You done sent your army to be getting me?"

303
00:11:34,460 --> 00:11:35,240
我直直的看着他
I looked him dead in the eye.

304
00:11:35,370 --> 00:11:36,460
我什么都不怕
I wasn't fearing nothing.

305
00:11:36,490 --> 00:11:39,460
我准备跟他斗个你死我活，直至现在我都是！
I was ready to tangle, just like I'm ready to tangle now!

306
00:11:39,990 --> 00:11:41,760
圣经说要经常警惕
Bible says be ever vigilant.

307
00:11:41,760 --> 00:11:44,200
所以我不会喝醉，我还要耳听八方
So, I don't get but so drunk. I got to keep watch.

308
00:11:44,200 --> 00:11:46,000
特洛伊当时进了慈善医院
Troy was right down there at mercy hospital.

309
00:11:46,070 --> 00:11:46,970
你记得他那次得了肺炎
You remember he had that pneumonia,

310
00:11:47,000 --> 00:11:49,300
还有发烧，躺在床上还说些有的没的
laying there with a fever, talking plumb out his head.

311
00:11:49,300 --> 00:11:50,540
当时死神站在那盯着我
And death standing there, staring at me,

312
00:11:50,540 --> 00:11:52,200
手握着镰刀
carrying that sickle in his hand.

313
00:11:52,210 --> 00:11:58,110
终于，他说：你想再活多一年吗？
Finally, he say, "you want to be bound over for another year?"

314
00:11:58,110 --> 00:12:00,280
他这样说
Just like that. He say,

315
00:12:00,280 --> 00:12:04,220
你想再活多一年吗？
"you want to be bound over for another year?"

316
00:12:04,220 --> 00:12:08,250
我说：去你的，我们现在就说清楚
I said, "bound over, hell! We can settle this right now."

317
00:12:08,260 --> 00:12:10,290
他听了后退后了点
He kinda fell back when I said that.

318
00:12:10,290 --> 00:12:11,760
我即时龙精虎猛
And all the cold went out of me.

319
00:12:11,760 --> 00:12:14,090
我伸手抢去他的镰刀
I reached down, I grabbed that sickle.

320
00:12:14,090 --> 00:12:15,560
我用尽力气扔走它
I threw it as far as I could throw it,

321
00:12:15,560 --> 00:12:17,400
然后我们开始埋身肉搏
and me and him commenced to wrestling.

322
00:12:17,400 --> 00:12:21,130
我们打了…六…三天三夜
We wrestled for... Carry the six... Three days and three nights!

323
00:12:21,140 --> 00:12:23,400
我不知道从哪儿来的力量
Now, I don't know where I got the strength from,

324
00:12:23,400 --> 00:12:25,270
因为他处于优势时
'cause every time he tried to get the best of me,

325
00:12:25,270 --> 00:12:28,070
我重新振作
I reached way deep down inside myself,

326
00:12:28,080 --> 00:12:29,410
并又得到对抗他的力量
found the strength to do him one better.

327
00:12:29,410 --> 00:12:31,210
