你住在我的房子里，吃我买回来的食物
You live in my house, fill your belly with my food,

997
00:41:58,540 --> 00:42:02,180
我照顾你是因为你是我的儿子啊
put your behind on my bed because you're my son.

998
00:42:02,180 --> 00:42:05,120
而不是我喜欢你，照顾你是我的职责
Not 'cause I like you. 'Cause it's my duty to take care of you.

999
00:42:05,120 --> 00:42:07,880
我得承担起这个责任
I owe a responsibility to you.

1000
00:42:07,890 --> 00:42:09,890
现在我就说清楚
Now, let's get this straight right here and now,

1001
00:42:09,890 --> 00:42:11,290
以免你将来又说同样的话
before it go along any further.

1002
00:42:11,290 --> 00:42:12,990
我不需要喜欢你
I ain't got to like you.

1003
00:42:12,990 --> 00:42:16,130
兰德先生每星期发薪给我不是因为他喜欢我
Mr. Rand don't give me my money come payday 'cause he like me.

1004
00:42:16,130 --> 00:42:19,230
是因为他欠我的
He give it to me 'cause he owe me.

1005
00:42:19,600 --> 00:42:21,300
现在我已给了所有我该给你的
Now I done give you everything I got to give you.

1006
00:42:21,300 --> 00:42:23,870
我把你带到这个世界上啊！
I give you your life!

1007
00:42:23,870 --> 00:42:25,800
你妈妈和我都商讨好各自的职责
Me and your mama worked that out between us,

1008
00:42:25,900 --> 00:42:28,610
而喜欢你不是我的工作之一
and liking your black ass wasn't part of the bargain.

1009
00:42:28,680 --> 00:42:29,780
你从今起别再
Now don't you go through life

1010
00:42:29,810 --> 00:42:32,310
担心别人是否喜欢你
worrying about whether somebody like you, or not.

1011
00:42:32,310 --> 00:42:35,580
你该想他们没有负了你
You best be making sure they're doing right by you.

1012
00:42:35,650 --> 00:42:36,950
- 明白了吗？ - 明白，先生
- You understand what I'm saying?  - Yes, sir.

1013
00:42:36,980 --> 00:42:40,980
那现在滚开，去A&P拿回你的工作
Then get the hell out of my face and get on down to that A&P!

1014
00:43:03,440 --> 00:43:06,640
你为何就不让那孩子打美式足球呢，特洛伊？
Why don't you go ahead and let the boy play football, Troy?

1015
00:43:06,650 --> 00:43:08,650
他只想像你一样在运动有点成就
He just want to be like you with the sports.

1016
00:43:08,650 --> 00:43:10,950
我不想他重蹈覆辙
I don't want him to be like me.

1017
00:43:10,950 --> 00:43:12,380
我想他走条和我完全不同的路
I want him to get as far away from my life

1018
00:43:12,450 --> 00:43:13,550
越不同越好
as he possibly can get.

1019
00:43:13,580 --> 00:43:16,020
你是我生命中唯一遇过的好事，罗斯
You the only decent thing ever happened to me, Rose.

1020
00:43:16,290 --> 00:43:17,990
我希望他找个像你一样好的女人
And I wish him that.

1021
00:43:18,290 --> 00:43:21,420
除此之外我不希望他像我一样
But I don't wish him nothing else from my life.

1022
00:43:22,390 --> 00:43:24,030
我在他出生的那天就决定
I decided 17 years ago,

1023
00:43:24,030 --> 00:43:26,400
那孩子不要参与什么运动
that boy wasn't gonna get involved in no sports.

1024
00:43:26,400 --> 00:43:28,200
在我明白运动里的不公之后
Not after what they did to me in the sports.

1025
00:43:28,200 --> 00:43:30,400
你为何就不承认你当时不能进职业联盟是因为年纪？
Why don't you just admit you were too old for the Major Leagues?

1026
00:43:30,400 --> 00:43:32,200
就承认一次？
For once, why don't you just admit that?

1027
00:43:32,200 --> 00:43:34,040
别跟我来年纪这套
Don't you come tellin' me I was too old.

1028
00:43:34,040 --> 00:43:37,270
是因为我是有色人种而已，我现在都五十三岁了
I just wasn't the right color. Hell, I'm 53 years old,

1029
00:43:37,280 --> 00:43:40,380
但我肯定我能打出比“S”的点二六九更好的成绩
I can do better than Selkirk's .269 right now.

1030
00:43:40,380 --> 00:43:43,010
过了四十岁还怎样打棒球？
How were you gonna play ball when you were over 40?

1031
00:43:43,020 --> 00:43:44,650
有时候你说的话真不合逻辑
Sometimes, I can't get no sense out of you.

1032
00:43:44,720 --> 00:43:45,820
我很清醒，女人
I got good sense, woman.

1033
00:43:45,850 --> 00:43:49,190
我清楚知道别让运动伤了他的身心
I got sense enough not to let that boy get hurt playing no sports.

1034
00:43:49,190 --> 00:43:50,950
你太疼爱他了
You mothering the boy too much.

1035
00:43:50,960 --> 00:43:53,120
让他老是担心别人是否喜欢自己
Worrying about whether people "like" him or not.

1036
00:43:53,130 --> 00:43:56,290
那孩子做的所有事，都是为了给你看
Everything that boy do, he do for you.

1037
00:43:56,300 --> 00:43:59,100
他想你称赞他，仅此而已
He wants you to say, "good job, son." That's all.

1038
00:43:59,300 --> 00:44:02,430
罗斯，我没时间做这些事，他好好的活着
I ain't got time for that, Rose. He's alive, he's healthy.

1039
00:44:02,430 --> 00:44:06,100
就得自己找出路，我也得继续自己的生活
He's got to make his own way. I made mine.

1040
00:44:06,100 --> 00:44:07,270
他将来出社会后
Ain't nobody gonna hold his hand

1041
00:44:07,270 --> 00:44:08,670
没有人会时常照顾他的
when he get out there in the world.

1042
00:44:08,670 --> 00:44:11,140
特洛伊，时代不同了
Times have changed, Troy.

1043
00:44:11,140 --> 00:44:13,240
人会变的
People change.

1044
00:44:13,250 --> 00:44:15,480
世界在变，而你根本不知道
The world changing, and you can't even see it.

1045
00:44:22,120 --> 00:44:25,020
女人，我尽我所能地工作
Woman, I do the best I can do.

1046
00:44:25,020 --> 00:44:26,290
每星期五我带着
I come in here every Friday,

1047
00:44:26,290 --> 00:44:29,230
一袋马铃薯和一桶猪油回来
I carry a sack of potatoes and a bucket of lard.

1048
00:44:29,230 --> 00:44:33,030
你们才得以不用工作
You all line up at the door with your hands out.

1049
00:44:33,030 --> 00:44:34,730
我连最后的钱都用在你们身上
I give you the lint from my pockets.

1050
00:44:34,730 --> 00:44:36,470
我付出了我的血汗
I give you my sweat and my blood.

1051
00:44:36,470 --> 00:44:39,270
我无法给你们同情，早已用光了
I ain't got no tears. I done spent them.

1052
00:44:39,270 --> 00:44:42,070
我们晚上到楼上做爱
We go upstairs in that room at night, I fall down on you

1053
00:44:42,070 --> 00:44:45,440
在你里面给了我唯一所剩的
and try to blast a hole into forever.

1054
00:44:45,440 --> 00:44:48,040
星期一早上起来，带着桌上煮好的午餐
I get up Monday morning, find my lunch on the table,

1055
00:44:48,050 --> 00:44:49,310
出去继续我的生活
go out and make my way.

1056
00:44:49,310 --> 00:44:53,720
试着捱到星期五
Find my strength to get me through to next Friday.

1057
00:44:53,720 --> 00:44:55,250
那就是我能给的，罗斯
That's all I got, Rose.

1058
00:44:58,260 --> 00:45:01,190
那已经是我能给你们的全部了
That's all I got to give.

1059
00:45:05,260 --> 00:45:07,030
已经没什么可以再给你们了！
Can't give nothing else!

1060
00:45:33,760 --> 00:45:35,160
马克森先生？
Mr. Maxson?

1061
00:45:38,100 --> 00:45:40,300
理事长想见你
Commissioner will see you now.

1062
00:45:47,100 --> 00:45:48,410
罗斯
Rose!

1063
00:45:51,310 --> 00:45:53,110
嘿，罗！
Hey, Ro!

1064
00:45:53,110 --> 00:45:57,410
我真想看到兰德先生当时的糗样
I wish I could've seen Mr. Rand's face when he told you.

1065
00:45:57,420 --> 00:46:00,350
他听了判决后都说不出话来了
He couldn't get it out his mouth. Liked to bit his tongue.

1066
00:46:00,350 --> 00:46:02,350
当他们叫我到理事长的办公室时
When they called me down there to the commissioner's office,

1067
00:46:02,350 --> 00:46:05,260
兰德像所有人一样都以为他们要炒了我
he thought they was gonna fire me, like everybody else.

1068
00:46:05,260 --> 00:46:07,090
我可没有这样想
Oh, I didn't think they was gonna fire you.

1069
00:46:07,090 --> 00:46:09,430
我以为他们要给你警告信
I thought they's gonna put you on the warning paper.

1070
00:46:09,430 --> 00:46:12,830
嘿，罗斯！对，兰德先生这下一定无话可说了
Hey, Rose! Yeah, Mr. Rand liked to bit his tongue.

1071
00:46:12,830 --> 00:46:15,130
我看到你跑到泰勒的酒吧
I see you run right down there to Taylors'

1072
00:46:15,130 --> 00:46:16,400
告诉那个叫艾伯塔的女子
and told that Alberta gal.

1073
00:46:16,400 --> 00:46:19,470
嘿，罗斯！我跟所有人都会说的，嘿，罗！
Hey, Rose! I told everybody. Hey, Ro!

1074
00:46:19,470 --> 00:46:21,500
我去那兑现支票[花钱]
I went down there to cash my check.

1075
00:46:21,600 --> 00:46:22,370
嘿！
Hey!

1076
00:46:22,370 --> 00:46:25,380
别叫了，我知道你回来了
Hush all that hollering. I know you out here.

1077
00:46:25,380 --> 00:46:27,280
理事长怎说了？
What they say down at the commissioner's office?

1078
00:46:27,280 --> 00:46:29,210
我叫你的时候你就该立刻回应我，女人
You supposed to come when I call you, woman.

1079
00:46:29,210 --> 00:46:30,380
博诺也懂
Bono will tell you that.

1080
00:46:30,380 --> 00:46:32,120
你叫露西尔时她不也立刻回应吗？
Don't Lucille come when you call her?

1081
00:46:32,120 --> 00:46:33,650
闭嘴吧老兄，我又不是狗
Man, hush your mouth. I ain't no dog.

1082
00:46:33,680 --> 00:46:34,420
说什么立刻回应你
Talk about come when you call me.

1083
00:46:34,450 --> 00:46:36,290
博诺，看到了吗？我以前有只狗
You hear this, Bono? I used to have me an old dog

1084
00:46:36,360 --> 00:46:37,460
也像这样自以为高人一等
get uppity like that.

1085
00:46:37,490 --> 00:46:40,160
你喊他来，他也不理会
You say, "come here, Blue,"he just lay there, look at you.

1086
00:46:40,160 --> 00:46:42,360
最后通常都是被追着打，为了教训他
End up getting a stick chasin' him away, trying to make him come.

1087
00:46:42,360 --> 00:46:43,860
我不在意你和你的狗
I ain't studying you and your dog.

1088
00:46:43,860 --> 00:46:45,600
我记得你总会唱起歌来
I remember you used to sing that old song.

1089
00:46:49,870 --> 00:46:51,700
没有人想听啊
Nobody wants to hear that old song.

1090
00:46:54,270 --> 00:46:56,370
他唱起来时，总让科丽到处跑
Used to have Cory runnin' around here singin' that song.

1091
00:46:56,370 --> 00:46:58,170
我也记得那首歌
Hell, I remember that song myself.

1092
00:47:03,180 --> 00:47:04,370
那是我爸爸的歌
That's my daddy's song.

1093
00:47:04,800 --> 00:47:06,190
他创作的
My daddy made up that song.

1094
00:47:06,420 --> 00:47:08,350
我才不在乎谁作的，没有人想听你唱的
I don't care who made it up. Don't nobody want to hear you sing it.

1095
00:47:10,290 --> 00:47:13,620
你这么兴奋回来，我就猜到他们没有炒了你
You come in here carrying on, I reckon they ain't fired you.

1096
00:47:13,630 --> 00:47:15,630
理事长到底说了什么？
What they say down there at the commissioner's office?

1097
00:47:15,630 --> 00:47:18,900
罗斯，听着，兰德先生在理事长会见我后
Look here, Rose. Mr. Rand called me in his office

1098
00:47:18,900 --> 00:47:21,460
叫我到他的办公室
after I got back from talkin' to them people down there.

1099
00:47:21,470 --> 00:47:24,130
他叫我进去并说
He called me in his office and told me...

1100
00:47:25,500 --> 00:47:27,170
他们要让我当司机！
They was making me a driver!

1101
00:47:27,170 --> 00:47:30,510
- 特洛伊，你在说笑吧！ - 不信问博诺
- Troy, you kidding!  - No, I ain't. Ask Bono.

1102
00:47:30,510 --> 00:47:31,640
那真好，特洛伊
That's great, Troy.

1103
00:47:31,640 --> 00:47:33,340
那你再不用跟那些人纠缠了
Now you don't have to hassle them people no more.

1104
00:47:33,350 --> 00:47:36,450
天啊，没想到今天你会来
Oh, hell. I didn't think I was gonna see you today.

1105
00:47:36,520 --> 00:47:37,620
我以为你在监狱里
I thought you was in jail.

1106
00:47:37,650 --> 00:47:40,480
听到消息说他们扫荡西佛的店
Got it all over the courier about them raiding Seefus' place

1107
00:47:40,490 --> 00:47:43,220
那个你跟那些不伦不类的家伙经常去的地方
where you be hanging out with all them thugs.

1108
00:47:43,220 --> 00:47:44,890
嘿，爸，那跟我没关系
Hey, pop, that ain't got nothing to do with me.

1109
00:47:44,960 --> 00:47:46,060
我没在那赌博
I don't go down there gambling.

1110
00:47:46,090 --> 00:47:48,220
我只是去那跟乐队交流
I just go down there to sit in with the band.

1111
00:47:48,230 --> 00:47:50,360
那赌博跟我沾不上关系
I ain't got nothing to do with the gambling part.

1112
00:47:50,360 --> 00:47:51,900
他们那里有些很好的音乐人
They got some good music down there.

1113
00:47:51,900 --> 00:47:53,630
那里只有流氓而已
They got some rogues is what they got.

1114
00:47:53,630 --> 00:47:55,670
博诺先生你还好吗？你好，罗斯
How you been, Mr. Bono? Hi, Rose.

1115
00:47:55,670 --> 00:47:58,540
我知道你今晚在克劳佛烧烤店有演出[爵士乐俱乐部]
I see where you playing down at the Crawford Grill tonight.

1116
00:47:58,540 --> 00:48:00,240
你怎么又不带邦妮来？
How come you ain't brought Bonnie like I told you?

1117
00:48:00,240 --> 00:48:01,340
你该带上她来
You shoulda brought Bonnie.

1118
00:48:01,340 --> 00:48:02,570
她很久没来过了
She ain't been by in a month of Sundays.

1119
00:48:02,570 --> 00:48:03,910
我刚巧路过而已
I was just in the neighborhood.

1120
00:48:03,910 --> 00:48:05,440
- 想着见你们一面  - 又来了
- Thought I'd stop by.  - Here it comes.

1121
00:48:05,440 --> 00:48:07,640
你爸爸升职了
Your daddy got a promotion on the rubbish.

1122
00:48:07,650 --> 00:48:10,250
他是第一个驾驶垃圾车的有色人种
He gonna be the first colored driver.

1123
00:48:10,250 --> 00:48:11,480
什么也不用做
Ain't got to do nothin' but sit up there

1124
00:48:11,480 --> 00:48:13,180
像白人一样坐着看报纸就行了
and read the paper, like them white fellas.

1125
00:48:13,190 --> 00:48:15,690
爸，如果你识字的话，那会是件好事
Hey, pop, if you knew how to read, you'd be all right.

1126
00:48:15,690 --> 00:48:18,420
不不，你指如果这老兄懂得驾驶的话
Nah, nah. You mean if the nigger knew how to drive,

1127
00:48:18,420 --> 00:48:19,560
那才是件好事
he'd be all right.

1128
00:48:19,590 --> 00:48:22,090
一直跟那些人争论驾车的问题
Been fighting with them people about driving

1129
00:48:22,320 --> 00:48:23,330
然而连驾照也没有
and ain't even got a license.

1130
00:48:23,330 --> 00:48:24,960
兰德先生知道你没有驾照的吧？
Mr. Rand know you ain't got no driver's license?

1131
00:48:25,030 --> 00:48:26,130
驾车很容易
Driving ain't nothing.

1132
00:48:26,160 --> 00:48:27,930
就是扭軚盘而已
All you do is point the truck where you want it to go.

1133
00:48:28,000 --> 00:48:29,200
并不难
Driving ain't nothing.

1134
00:48:29,230 --> 00:48:31,170
他们知道你没有驾照吗？
Do they know you ain't got no driver's license?

1135
00:48:31,170 --> 00:48:32,470
那才是我问的
That's what I'm talkin' about.

1136
00:48:32,500 --> 00:48:33,510
我不是问你驾驶是否容易
I ain't asked if driving was easy.

1137
00:48:33,640 --> 00:48:35,670
我问你兰德先生是否知道你没有驾照一事
I asked if Mr. Rand know you ain't got no driver's license.

1138
00:48:35,740 --> 00:48:36,940
那人没必要知道我的事
The man ain't got to know my business.

1139
00:48:36,970 --> 00:48:39,280
待他发现时我已经有两三个驾照了
Time he find out, I have two or three of them driver's license.

1140
00:48:39,280 --> 00:48:41,280
- 听着，爸  - 我就知道你会这么说
- Say, look here, pop.  - I knew it was coming.

1141
00:48:41,280 --> 00:48:43,280
我知道你要说什么
I knew what kinda "look here, pop" that was.

1142
00:48:43,280 --> 00:48:44,650
那小子又要问我拿钱了
Nigger finna ask me for some money.

1143
00:48:44,650 --> 00:48:46,520
今天是星期五，又是我的发薪日
It's Friday night, it's my payday.

1144
00:48:46,520 --> 00:48:50,290
那些没被拘捕的流氓会在林荫大道流连
All them rogues down on the Avenue, the ones that ain't in jail,

1145
00:48:50,290 --> 00:48:52,960
里昂赶着去跟他们会合
and Lyons is hopping in his shoes to get down there with them.

1146
00:48:53,030 --> 00:48:54,030
听着，爸
Now, see, pop,

1147
00:48:54,160 --> 00:48:56,590
如果你让别人说完他要说的
if you gave somebody else a chance to talk sometime,

1148
00:48:56,600 --> 00:49:00,400
你就会知道我要还你答应过的十块
you'd see I was fixing to pay you back your $10 like I told you.

1149
00:49:00,400 --> 00:49:03,530
拿着，我说过待邦妮发薪了我会还你的
Here. I told you I'd pay you when Bonnie got paid.

1150
00:49:03,540 --> 00:49:05,740
不，你自己留着那十块，存到银行里
No, you keep that $10. Put it in the bank.

1151
00:49:05,740 --> 00:49:07,540
下次你觉得又要来这里向我拿钱时
Next time you feel like you wanna come by here

1152
00:49:07,540 --> 00:49:09,370
你就从银行拿出这十块
and ask me for somethin', you go down there and get that.

1153
00:49:09,510 --> 00:49:11,310
拿着属于你的十块吧，爸
Here you go your $10, pop.

1154
00:49:11,410 --> 00:49:12,640
我说过我不想你给我
I told you, I don't want you to give me nothing.

1155
00:49:12,710 --> 00:49:13,810
我只想借而已
I just wanted to borrow $10.

1156
00:49:13,840 --> 00:49:16,710
不，你留着下次用
No, you keep that for the next time you want to ask me.

1157
00:49:16,720 --> 00:49:18,350
别这样，爸，拿着吧
Come on, pop, here go your $10.

1158
00:49:18,350 --> 00:49:21,480
特洛伊，你为何不让那孩子还钱？
Troy, why don't you let the boy pay you back?

1159
00:49:24,320 --> 00:49:26,720
你替他拿吧，罗斯，如果你不拿
Here you go, Rose. If you don't take it,

1160
00:49:26,730 --> 00:49:28,730
接下来六个月他又要不断唠叨此事了
I'm gonna hear about it for the next six months.

1161
00:49:28,730 --> 00:49:30,560
你也可以顺道给出你的那份薪金，特洛伊
You can hand yours over, too, Troy.

1162
00:49:30,560 --> 00:49:32,330
博诺，你看到他们怎对待我了吗
You see this, Bono? You see how they do me?

1163
00:49:32,330 --> 00:49:34,030
看到，露西尔也是这样做
Yeah, Lucille do me the same way.

1164
00:49:43,340 --> 00:49:45,340
嘿，是特洛伊的儿子啊
Hey. Hey, there's Troy's boy!

1165
00:49:45,340 --> 00:49:46,640
加布叔叔，你最近好吗？
How you doing, Uncle Gabe?

1166
00:49:46,650 --> 00:49:48,410
里昂
Lyons!

1167
00:49:50,050 --> 00:49:52,580
万兽之王
The king of the jungle!

1168
00:49:52,750 --> 00:49:55,750
嘿，罗斯，我有朵玫瑰花给你
Rose. Hey, Rose, I got a flower for you.

1169
00:49:55,750 --> 00:49:58,450
我亲自摘的，就跟你名字一样的玫瑰
I picked it myself. That's the same rose like you is.

1170
00:49:58,460 --> 00:50:00,060
你真有心，加布
Aw, that's right nice of you, Gabe.

1171
00:50:00,060 --> 00:50:01,660
加布叔叔，你最近在做什么？
What you been doing, Uncle Gabe?

1172
00:50:01,660 --> 00:50:05,400
噢，我一直在追赶地狱之犬
Oh, I been chasing hellhounds and waiting for the time

1173
00:50:05,400 --> 00:50:07,360
并等着告诉圣彼得打开天堂的门
to tell Saint Peter to open the gates.

1174
00:50:07,370 --> 00:50:08,800
你在追赶地狱之犬？
You been chasing hellhounds, huh?

1175
00:50:08,800 --> 00:50:10,700
你做得很正确
Well, you doing the right thing, Uncle Gabe.

1176
00:50:10,700 --> 00:50:13,770
- 总有人要去赶走他们  - 是的，我也知道
- Somebody's got to chase 'em.  - Oh, yeah, I know it.

1177
00:50:13,770 --> 00:50:16,740
魔鬼很强大，不是那么容易打败
The devil's strong. The devil ain't no pushover.

1178
00:50:16,740 --> 00:50:19,380
地狱之犬一直在寻找人类的气息[应为sniff，非snip]
Hellhounds snipping at everybody's heels.

1179
00:50:19,380 --> 00:50:22,050
但我已经准备好喇叭，等待审判日的来临
But I got my trumpet waiting on the judgment time.

1180
00:50:22,050 --> 00:50:23,750
为了哈米吉多顿之战作准备吗？[圣经中世界末日最后一战]
Waiting on the Battle of Armageddon, huh?

1181
00:50:23,750 --> 00:50:25,820
噢，那眨眼就会结束
Oh, ain't gonna be too much of a battle

1182
00:50:25,820 --> 00:50:29,550
当上帝挥动审判之剑时
when god get to waving that judgment sword.

1183
00:50:29,550 --> 00:50:31,650
如果天堂的门关上的话，那时候人们就得费时
But the people's gonna have a hell of a time

1184
00:50:31,660 --> 00:50:34,420
等待进入天堂了
trying to get into heaven if them gates ain't open.

1185
00:50:34,430 --> 00:50:35,790
你听到这吗，爸？
You hear this, pop?

1186
00:50:36,490 --> 00:50:37,590
加布叔叔，你人真好
Uncle Gabe, you all right.

1187
00:50:37,600 --> 00:50:38,660
里昂
Lyons.

1188
00:50:41,670 --> 00:50:42,870
万兽之王
The king of the jungle!

1189
00:50:43,370 --> 00:50:44,300
加布，你留下来吃晚餐吗？
You stayin' for supper, Gabe?

1190
00:50:44,430 --> 00:50:45,370
你要我煮你的份吗？
You want me to fix you a plate?

1191
00:50:45,400 --> 00:50:48,500
我要份三明治就好了，不用煮我的份
I'll just take a sandwich, Rose. I don't want no plate.

1192
00:50:48,510 --> 00:50:50,610
我喜欢用双手拿着来吃，三明治好了
I want to eat with my hands. I'll take a sandwich.

1193
00:50:50,610 --> 00:50:53,080
你呢里昂？留下吗？在煮牛小排呢
What about you, Lyons? You stayin'? Got some short ribs cooking.

1194
00:50:53,080 --> 00:50:56,650
不了，我通常在演出完结后才用餐的
Nah. I won't eat nothing till after we finish playing.

1195
00:50:57,380 --> 00:50:59,420
你应该来看看我演出，爸
You ought to come down, listen to me play, pop.

1196
00:50:59,420 --> 00:51:01,650
噢，我不喜欢那些像中国音乐一样的嘈音
Oh, I don't like all that Chinese music, all that noise.

1197
00:51:01,650 --> 00:51:05,120
去洗手吧，加布，我现在弄三明治
Go in there and wash up, Gabe. I'll fix you a sandwich.

1198
00:51:05,120 --> 00:51:07,820
特洛伊在生我的气
Troy mad at me.

1199
00:51:07,830 --> 00:51:09,430
你为何生他的气？
What you mad at Uncle Gabe for?

1200
00:51:09,430 --> 00:51:10,560
他以为特洛伊为了
He think Troy mad at him

1201
00:51:10,560 --> 00:51:12,430
他搬到珀尔那里而生气
'cause he moved over there to Miss Pearl's.

1202
00:51:12,430 --> 00:51:14,530
我才没有生气，他可以住他想住的地方
I ain't mad at the man. He can live where he want to live at.

1203
00:51:14,530 --> 00:51:16,700
他为何搬到那里？珀尔小姐任何人都不喜欢
Well, what he move over there for? Miss Pearl don't like nobody.

1204
00:51:16,700 --> 00:51:18,570
噢，她不介意他在，还对他颇好
Oh, she don't mind him none. She treat him real nice.

1205
00:51:18,640 --> 00:51:19,740
她就不允许他唱歌而已
She just don't allow all that singing.

1206
00:51:19,770 --> 00:51:22,670
她不介意他在为她付租金，仅此而已
She don't mind that rent he be paying. That's what she don't mind.

1207
00:51:22,670 --> 00:51:24,440
特洛伊，我不想再跟你讨论此事
Troy, I ain't goin' through that with you no more.

1208
00:51:24,440 --> 00:51:26,140
他搬到那因为他想要有自己的地方
He moved over there 'cause he wanted his own place.

1209
00:51:26,210 --> 00:51:27,310
他可以随他所想的做
He can come and go as he please.

1210
00:51:27,340 --> 00:51:29,580
他可以在这里做他想做的，我也不介意
He can come and go as he please here. I wasn't stoppin' him.

1211
00:51:29,580 --> 00:51:30,780
我也没规定他什么
I wasn't putting no rules on the man.

1212
00:51:30,780 --> 00:51:32,620
你明知道那是两码子的事
That ain't the same thing, and you know it.

1213
00:51:33,050 --> 00:51:34,590
我不想再讨论这话题
Now that's the last I wanna hear about that.

1214
00:51:34,620 --> 00:51:36,450
我不想再听到加布和珀尔小姐之间的事
I don't wanna hear nothin' else about Gabe and Miss Pearl.

1215
00:51:36,450 --> 00:51:37,490
还有下周…
And next week...

1216
00:51:37,490 --> 00:51:39,320
我准备好了，罗斯
I'm ready for my sandwich, Rose.

1217
00:51:39,320 --> 00:51:41,420
还有下周，当从学校来的负责人到来
And next week, when that recruiter come from that school,

1218
00:51:41,430 --> 00:51:43,890
我要你签署让科丽进美式足球队
I want you to sign that paper and go on and let Cory play football.

1219
00:51:43,900 --> 00:51:45,800
我不想再听你说起此事
That'll be the last I have to hear about that.

1220
00:51:50,530 --> 00:51:52,600
科丽被录取了？他要到哪所学校？
Cory got recruited? What school he goin' to?

1221
00:51:52,600 --> 00:51:54,170
我不想再理会科丽的事
I ain't thinking about Cory nothing.

1222
00:51:54,170 --> 00:51:56,570
那小子把这里当成他的地方
Boy walking around here smelling his piss,

1223
00:51:56,570 --> 00:51:57,910
以为可以为所欲为
thinking he gonna do what he want to do,

1224
00:51:57,910 --> 00:52:00,480
不听我的说话
irregardless of what I say.

1225
00:52:00,480 --> 00:52:02,710
博诺，听着，我离开理事长的办公室后
Look here, Bono, I left the commissioner's office

1226
00:52:02,710 --> 00:52:04,180
去了A&P那里
and went down to the A&P.

1227
00:52:04,180 --> 00:52:06,620
那小子根本没在那工作，他跟我说谎了
That boy ain't workin' down there, he lied to me.

1228
00:52:06,620 --> 00:52:09,890
说他取回了工作，周末得上班什么的
Tellin' me he got his job back, tellin' me he workin' weekend,

1229
00:52:09,890 --> 00:52:11,620
说他课后在上班
tellin' me he workin' after school.

1230
00:52:11,620 --> 00:52:13,820
斯塔维茨基说他根本没来上班
Mr. Stawicki says he ain't working down there at all.

1231
00:52:13,900 --> 00:52:15,000
科丽只是长大了而已
Cory just growing up.

1232
00:52:15,030 --> 00:52:17,490
他有了自己的想法，不能再听你说的
He just bustin' at the seams, tryin' to fill out your shoes.

1233
00:52:17,570 --> 00:52:18,670
我才不在意他想什么
I don't care what he doing.

1234
00:52:18,700 --> 00:52:20,760
当他到了反叛期
When he get to the place where he want to disobey me,

1235
00:52:20,770 --> 00:52:23,900
那就是出外打拼的时候了，博诺也懂
then it's time for him to move on. Bono will tell you that.

1236
00:52:23,900 --> 00:52:25,740
我肯定他不能违抗他父亲后
I bet he ain't never disobeyed his daddy

1237
00:52:25,740 --> 00:52:27,770
不用受罚
without paying the consequences.

1238
00:52:27,770 --> 00:52:29,940
我根本没机会违抗他
I ain't never had the chance.

1239
00:52:29,940 --> 00:52:33,780
我父亲到处走，我根本没看过他
My daddy came on through, but I ain't never knew him to see him.

1240
00:52:33,780 --> 00:52:36,580
或者他在想什么，去哪了
Or what he had on his mind, or where he went.

1241
00:52:36,580 --> 00:52:40,450
就四海为家，寻找新大陆
Just moving on through. Searching out the new land.

1242
00:52:40,920 --> 00:52:43,550
那就是以前的人用的
That's what the old folks used to call it.

1243
00:52:43,560 --> 00:52:46,890
一个人要是到处搬，不停换女人
See a fella moving around from place to place, woman to woman,

1244
00:52:46,890 --> 00:52:49,560
他们叫这“寻找新大陆”
they call it "searching out the new land."

1245
00:52:49,560 --> 00:52:51,030
我也不清楚他有没有找到
I can't say if he ever found it.

1246
00:52:51,800 --> 00:52:54,560
我来到这地方，也不想有孩子
I come along, didn't want no kids.

1247
00:52:54,800 --> 00:52:56,830
我也不知道我能否安定下来
I didn't know if I was gonna be in one place long enough

1248
00:52:56,840 --> 00:52:58,900
当个爸爸
to fix on 'em right as their daddy.

1249
00:52:58,900 --> 00:53:01,200
我想不如还是寻找新大陆算了
I figured I was going searching, too.

1250
00:53:01,210 --> 00:53:03,570
没想过我跟露西尔在一起的时间
As it turn out, I been hooked up with Lucille

1251
00:53:03,580 --> 00:53:05,910
也几乎有你爸爸和罗斯在一起那么久了
for near about as long as your daddy been with Rose.

1252
00:53:05,910 --> 00:53:08,210
已经十六年了
Going on 16 years.

1253
00:53:08,210 --> 00:53:09,980
有时候我真希望自己不认识我的父亲
Sometimes, I wish I'd never known my daddy.

1254
00:53:09,980 --> 00:53:13,950
他不在意孩子过得怎样，对他来说毫不重要
He ain't cared nothing about no kids. A kid to him wasn't nothing.

1255
00:53:14,250 --> 00:53:17,650
他只想你快点成人
All he wanted you to do was learn how to walk,

1256
00:53:17,730 --> 00:53:18,830
好让你能去工作赚钱给他
so he could start you to working.

1257
00:53:18,860 --> 00:53:23,030
吃饭时，他总先吃，你只吃他剩下的
Come to eating, he ate first. Anything left over, that's what you got.

1258
00:53:23,030 --> 00:53:26,500
他会吃掉所有东西，而你只分到那么一点
Man would sit down, eat two chickens, and give you the wing.

1259
00:53:26,500 --> 00:53:29,700
爸，别胡说了，天下父母都会让子女吃饱
You ought to stop that, pop. Everybody feed their kids.

1260
00:53:29,700 --> 00:53:32,840
不管时势有多艰难，天下父母都疼爱子女
No matter how hard times is, everybody care about their kids.

1261
00:53:32,840 --> 00:53:34,040
确保他们三餐温饱
Make sure they have something to eat.

1262
00:53:34,040 --> 00:53:35,940
我父亲唯一在意的
Only thing my daddy cared about

1263
00:53:35,940 --> 00:53:37,810
就是叫我们搬那一卷卷的棉花给鲁宾先生
was getting them bales of cotton in to Mr. Lubin.

1264
00:53:37,810 --> 00:53:39,910
那是他唯一在意的事
That's the only thing that mattered to him.

1265
00:53:39,910 --> 00:53:42,250
以前我都在想他为何还活着
Sometimes, I used to wonder why he was still living,

1266
00:53:42,250 --> 00:53:44,950
为何魔鬼还没带走他
why the devil hadn't come and got him.

1267
00:53:44,950 --> 00:53:46,950
快把棉花搬到鲁宾先生那
"Get them bales of cotton in to Mr. Lubin."

1268
00:53:46,950 --> 00:53:48,580
后来才知道我父亲欠鲁宾钱
Find out he owe him money.

1269
00:53:48,590 --> 00:53:49,720
当他知道此地不宜久留时
He should have just went on and left

1270
00:53:49,720 --> 00:53:50,750
他就该跑路
when he saw he couldn't get nowhere.

1271
00:53:50,830 --> 00:53:51,930
至少我会那样做
That's what I would've done.

1272
00:53:51,960 --> 00:53:54,860
他怎留下十一个孩子就走？还有走去哪？
How he gonna leave with 11 kids? And where he gonna go?

1273
00:53:54,860 --> 00:53:57,990
他只懂耕作，他根本无路可逃
He ain't knew nothing but how to farm. No, he was trapped.

1274
00:53:58,600 --> 00:54:01,730
我想他也知道，但我也会为他说一句…
I think he knew it, too. But I'll say this for him...

1275
00:54:01,730 --> 00:54:03,630
他觉得他有责任照顾我们
He felt a responsibility toward us.

1276
00:54:03,640 --> 00:54:05,700
虽然不像我预期一样体贴
May not have treated us like I felt he should have,

1277
00:54:05,700 --> 00:54:07,670
但他要是没有良心
but without that responsibility,

1278
00:54:07,670 --> 00:54:09,710
大可以留下我们，自己跑路
he could have run off and left us,

1279
00:54:09,710 --> 00:54:10,970
再另起炉灶
made his own way.

1280
00:54:10,980 --> 00:54:12,610
很多人也这样
A lot of them did.

1281
00:54:12,610 --> 00:54:14,040
你说你父亲的那一代吗？
Back in those days, what you talkin' about?

1282
00:54:14,050 --> 00:54:15,880
他们每天离开房子
They walk out their front door

1283
00:54:15,880 --> 00:54:19,080
无论多日晒雨淋，都在街上一直走
and take off down one road or another and just keep on walkin'.

1284
00:54:19,080 --> 00:54:21,080
对，这才像话
There you go. That's what I'm talkin' about.

1285
00:54:21,090 --> 00:54:24,720
一直走到他们遇到下一间房子
Just keep on walking till they come to something else.

1286
00:54:24,720 --> 00:54:27,990
你没听过大迁徙吗？[一战时黑人从美国南部迁北]
Ain't you never heard of nobody having the walking blues?

1287
00:54:27,990 --> 00:54:30,760
那就是你叫那些跑路的人
Now, that's what you call it when you just take off like that.

1288
00:54:30,760 --> 00:54:34,660
我父亲不是你说的那种
My daddy ain't had no walking blues. What you talking about?

1289
00:54:34,670 --> 00:54:36,030
他留下来了
He stayed right there with his family,

1290
00:54:36,900 --> 00:54:40,900
但他坏事做尽
but he was just as evil as he could be!

1291
00:54:40,910 --> 00:54:44,740
我妈妈接受不了他和他的性格
My mama couldn't stand him. Couldn't stand that evilness.

1292
00:54:44,740 --> 00:54:47,780
我八岁时她就离开了
She run off when I was about eight.

1293
00:54:47,780 --> 00:54:50,910
她有一晚静悄悄的走，跟我说她会回来
She sneaked off one night, told me she was coming back for me.

1294
00:54:50,920 --> 00:54:52,780
自那我就再没有见过她
I ain't never seen her no more.

1295
00:54:52,780 --> 00:54:56,950
他有过的女人终究都会离开他，他不是个好人
All his women run off and left him. He wasn't good for nobody.

1296
00:54:57,590 --> 00:54:59,060
轮到我离家的时候
My turn come to head out.

1297
00:54:59,060 --> 00:55:00,660
我当时十四岁
I was 14,

1298
00:55:00,660 --> 00:55:03,660
跟乔·康纳尔的女儿打得火热
got to sniffing around Joe Canewell's daughter.

1299
00:55:04,860 --> 00:55:07,100
我们家有只老骡子叫“灰色男孩”
We had this old mule called "Greyboy".

1300
00:55:07,100 --> 00:55:09,630
我父亲叫我出去耕作
My daddy sent me out to do some plowing.

1301
00:55:09,630 --> 00:55:13,100
让我有机会跟乔·康纳尔的女儿谈谈情
I got to fooling around with Joe Canewell's daughter.

1302
00:55:13,100 --> 00:55:16,670
我们找到了一个隐蔽的地方抚摸大家
Found us a nice spot, got real cozy with each other.

1303
00:55:16,670 --> 00:55:19,840
她当时十三岁，所以我们都知道大家发育了
She was about 13, so we done figured we grown anyway.

1304
00:55:19,840 --> 00:55:22,110
我们在溪河附近，互相抚摸
So, we were down there by the creek, enjoying ourselves,

1305
00:55:22,110 --> 00:55:23,810
把正事都放一边
ain't thinking about nothing.

1306
00:55:23,820 --> 00:55:26,080
怎料绑着“灰色男孩”的绳子松开了
Didn't know Greyboy had gotten loose,

1307
00:55:26,080 --> 00:55:29,750
它跑回家里，我父亲就知道事有蹊跷
wandered back to the house, and my daddy was lookin' for me.

1308
00:55:29,890 --> 00:55:33,620
他找到我们时，看到我们还在抚摸大家
So, we down there enjoying ourselves when he come up on us.

1309
00:55:33,630 --> 00:55:35,730
我们不知所措
Surprised us.

1310
00:55:35,730 --> 00:55:38,130
他拿着骡子身上的皮带
Had them leather straps off that mule,

1311
00:55:38,130 --> 00:55:41,360
开始不停地打我
commenced to whupping me like there was no tomorrow.

1312
00:55:41,370 --> 00:55:44,030
我站起来，当时心感侮辱又愤怒
I jump up. I'm mad, embarrassed.

1313
00:55:44,700 --> 00:55:46,970
又很害怕他
I was scared of my daddy.

1314
00:55:46,970 --> 00:55:49,010
他开始打我时
Now, when he commenced to whipping on me,

1315
00:55:49,010 --> 00:55:50,870
很自然地我就逃跑吧
quite naturally, I run to get out of the way.

1316
00:55:50,880 --> 00:55:53,710
我想他是因为我没有完成工作而生气
Now, I think he's mad 'cause I ain't done my work.

1317
00:55:53,710 --> 00:55:56,150
但我看到他故意让我落跑
But I see where he's chasing me off,

1318
00:55:56,150 --> 00:55:58,180
然后想去独占这个女孩
so he can have the gal for himself.

1319
00:55:59,750 --> 00:56:01,920
当我想透了
When I see what the matter of it was,

1320
00:56:02,750 --> 00:56:06,990
我变得不再害怕他，自那，我成为了一个男人
I lost all fear of my daddy, and right there, I became a man.

1321
00:56:06,990 --> 00:56:09,660
才十四岁
Fourteen years of age.

1322
00:56:09,660 --> 00:56:12,660
是时候轮到我作主了
Now, it's my turn to run him off.

1323
00:56:12,660 --> 00:56:14,400
我拿起他刚才用的皮带
I picked up them same reins he used on me.

1324
00:56:14,400 --> 00:56:18,030
然后开始打起他来
I picked up them reins, I commenced to whupping on him.

1325
00:56:19,000 --> 00:56:21,270
那女孩落荒而逃
Gal jump up, she run off.

1326
00:56:23,140 --> 00:56:24,710
当他转过来看着我时
When he turned to face me,

1327
00:56:24,710 --> 00:56:26,680
我终于知道为何魔鬼没有带走他
I knew why the devil never come and get him

1328
00:56:26,680 --> 00:56:28,840
因为他就是魔鬼
'cause he was the devil himself.

1329
00:56:30,010 --> 00:56:32,750
我忘了之后发生什么了
I don't know what happened.

1330
00:56:32,750 --> 00:56:35,950
我醒过来，躺在溪河旁
I woke up, laying there by the creek,

1331
00:56:35,950 --> 00:56:39,790
我们养的老狗布卢，它在舔我的脸
and Blue, this old dog we had, he was licking my face.

1332
00:56:39,790 --> 00:56:42,890
我的双眼肿极了
Both my eyes were swoll shut.

1333
00:56:42,890 --> 00:56:44,830
我以为我瞎了，什么都看不到
I thought I was blind, I couldn't see nothing.

1334
00:56:44,830 --> 00:56:48,700
就躺在那里哭
I just laid there and cried.

1335
00:56:54,000 --> 00:56:57,010
我也不知道该怎办
And I didn't know what I was gonna do.

1336
00:56:57,010 --> 00:57:01,710
但我知道是时候离家出走了
But I knew the time had come for me to leave my daddy's house.

1337
00:57:02,810 --> 00:57:05,110
突然间我感觉到世界之大
Suddenly, the world got big, and...

1338
00:57:08,090 --> 00:57:12,120
费了我很多时间才弄清楚
It was a long time before I could cut it down to where I could handle it.

1339
00:57:13,820 --> 00:57:16,790
弄清楚的期间，我发现
Part of that cutting down was where I got to the place

1340
00:57:16,790 --> 00:57:18,830
其实他在我心底下，在怒吼着想出来
where I could feel him kicking in my blood,

1341
00:57:18,830 --> 00:57:20,230
而我和他之所以不同
and I knew the only thing that separated us

1342
00:57:20,230 --> 00:57:22,770
只是我们不是生于同一个时代而已
was a matter of a few years.

1343
00:57:25,740 --> 00:57:27,000
加布叔叔，你在吃什么？
What you got there, Uncle Gabe?

1344
00:57:27,940 --> 00:57:29,470
我在吃火腿三明治
I got me a ham sandwich.

1345
00:57:29,470 --> 00:57:31,840
罗斯给我弄了火腿三明治
Rose gave me a ham sandwich.

1346
00:57:34,080 --> 00:57:36,250
除了加布里埃尔外，我没再联系家里的人
I lost touch with everybody except Gabriel.

1347
00:57:41,180 --> 00:57:42,250
但…
But...

1348
00:57:45,960 --> 00:57:47,920
我希望他已经死了
I hope he's dead.

1349
00:57:52,030 --> 00:57:54,860
我希望他能找到点安慰
I hope he found some peace.

1350
00:57:54,870 --> 00:57:57,030
真是个沉重的故事，爸
That's a heavy story, pop.

1351
00:57:58,140 --> 00:58:02,100
我都不知道你十四岁就离家了
I didn't know you left home when you was 14.

1352
00:58:02,110 --> 00:58:04,170
十四岁太早独立了
Fourteen's kinda young to be on your own.

1353
00:58:04,180 --> 00:58:06,180
要是我的话真不知道该怎办
I don't know what I would've done.

1354
00:58:06,980 --> 00:58:09,850
我在那溪河站了起来，向莫比尔出发
Well, I got up from that creek, walked on down to Mobile.

1355
00:58:09,850 --> 00:58:13,520
我不想再耕作了，我想我在城市会找到更好的工作
I was through with farming. I figured I'd do better in the cities.

1356
00:58:13,520 --> 00:58:15,320
所以我徒步走了两百英里到莫比尔
So, I walked the 200 miles to Mobile.

1357
00:58:15,320 --> 00:58:17,990
等下，你才没有徒步走两百英里，爸
Wait a minute, you ain't walked no 200 miles, pop.

1358
00:58:19,120 --> 00:58:21,190
没有人想这样做
Ain't nobody gonna walk no 200 miles.

1359
00:58:21,190 --> 00:58:23,230
那是段很长的距离啊！
You talking about some walking there!

1360
00:58:23,230 --> 00:58:26,100
以前唯一到其他地方的方法就是徒步
That's the only way you got anywhere back in them days.

1361
00:58:26,100 --> 00:58:29,060
妈的，我会选择搭便车
Shit! Damn if I wouldn't have hitched a ride with somebody.

1362
00:58:29,070 --> 00:58:30,870
哪来的便车？
Who you gonna hitch it with?

1363
00:58:30,870 --> 00:58:32,840
那时候才没有现在的车和科技
There ain't no cars and things like they got now.

1364
00:58:32,840 --> 00:58:34,270
当时是一九一八年
We talking about 1918.

1365
00:58:34,270 --> 00:58:36,070
你们在这里聊什么？
What you all out here gettin' into?

1366
00:58:36,070 --> 00:58:38,240
我跟里昂说他现时的生活比以前好多了
I'm telling Lyons how good he got it.

1367
00:58:38,240 --> 00:58:39,840
他根本不知道我在说什么
He don't know nothing about this I'm talking.

1368
00:58:39,840 --> 00:58:41,140
里昂，刚才邦妮打来了
Lyons, that was Bonnie on the phone.

1369
00:58:41,150 --> 00:58:42,550
她说你约好了去接她下班
She says you supposed to pick her up.

1370
00:58:42,550 --> 00:58:44,280
知道了，罗斯
Yeah, okay, Rose.

1371
00:58:44,280 --> 00:58:47,120
我到了莫比尔
I walked on down to Mobile,

1372
00:58:47,120 --> 00:58:50,550
搭了驶向这边来的人便车
hitched up with some fellows that was coming up this way.

1373
00:58:50,560 --> 00:58:52,190
到了才发现
Got up here and found out,

1374
00:58:52,190 --> 00:58:53,960
不但找不到工作
not only could you not get a job,

1375
00:58:53,960 --> 00:58:55,360
也找不到住处
you couldn't find no place to live.

1376
00:58:55,360 --> 00:58:58,290
我以为自己自由了
I thought I was in freedom.

1377
00:58:58,300 --> 00:59:00,960
有色人种都住在里弗班克[加州城市]
Colored folks living down there on the Riverbanks

1378
00:59:00,970 --> 00:59:03,170
随便哪里都好
in whatever kind of shelter they could find for themselves.

1379
00:59:03,170 --> 00:59:05,900
有些在桥下睡
Right down there under the Brady Street Bridge.

1380
00:59:06,100 --> 00:59:09,370
有些在自己用木条和沥青纸搭建的帐篷睡
Living down there in shacks made out of sticks and tar paper.

1381
00:59:10,310 --> 00:59:12,210
那时候我都要崩溃了
Messed around down there.

1382
00:59:12,210 --> 00:59:14,940
无恶不作，开始偷窃
Went from bad to worse. Started stealing.

1383
00:59:14,950 --> 00:59:17,350
开始时是食物，然后我想到偷钱
First, it was food. Then I figure I steal me some money,

1384
00:59:17,350 --> 00:59:20,120
可以买食物，鞋等
I can buy me some food, buy me some shoes, too.

1385
00:59:20,250 --> 00:59:22,180
一样接一样，最后遇见你的妈妈
One thing led to another. Met your mama.

1386
00:59:22,390 --> 00:59:24,990
当时还小，急着想成为个男人
I was young, anxious to be a man.

1387
00:59:25,320 --> 00:59:27,960
我遇到你妈妈后有了你，怎办了？
I met your mama and had you. Why'd I do that for?

1388
00:59:27,960 --> 00:59:30,260
我得多养两人
Now, I got to worry about feeding you and her.

1389
00:59:30,260 --> 00:59:32,030
得要偷更多才行
Got to steal three times as much.

1390
00:59:32,860 --> 00:59:36,170
我有一天在外面，想着对谁下手
I went out one day looking for somebody to rob.

1391
00:59:36,170 --> 00:59:37,430
对，我当时是个小偷
That's what I was, I was a robber.

1392
00:59:38,170 --> 00:59:39,970
我不会隐瞒
I'mma tell you the truth.

1393
00:59:39,970 --> 00:59:42,000
直至今天我还是心感惭愧，但那是事实
I'm ashamed of it today, but it's the truth.

1394
00:59:42,940 --> 00:59:44,940
我找到目标，掏出了我的小刀
I went to rob this fella, I pull out my knife.

1395
00:59:44,940 --> 00:59:47,080
他拿出了枪，想也不想就射在我胸口上
He pulled out a gun, shot me in the chest.

1396
00:59:47,080 --> 00:59:48,240
那感觉
It felt like somebody had taken

1397
00:59:48,250 --> 00:59:50,280
就像有人拿着灼热的铁块烙印在我身上
a hot branding iron and laid it on me.

1398
00:59:50,280 --> 00:59:53,350
他射了我之后，我跳上前以小刀还击
Now, when he shot me, I jumped at him with my knife,

1399
00:59:55,250 --> 00:59:57,220
他们说我杀了他
and they say I killed him.

1400
00:59:57,220 --> 00:59:59,290
让我坐了十五年监牢
Locked me up, put me in the penitentiary for 15 years.

1401
00:59:59,290 --> 01:00:00,960
我在里面认识了博诺
That's where I met Bono.

1402
01:00:01,220 --> 01:00:03,630
学会了打棒球
Where I learned how to play baseball.

1403
01:00:03,630 --> 01:00:05,230
出来后才发现你妈妈带走了你
Got out that place, and your mama had taken you,

1404
01:00:05,230 --> 01:00:07,260
在一个没有我的环境下继续生活
went on to make a life without me.

1405
01:00:07,270 --> 01:00:09,370
十五年是段很长的时间
Fifteen years was a long time for her to wait.

1406
01:00:09,370 --> 01:00:12,370
但那十五年让我改正了
But that 15 years cured me of that robbing stuff.

1407
01:00:12,370 --> 01:00:13,000
罗斯会告诉你
Rose'll tell you.

1408
01:00:13,000 --> 01:00:15,240
我再遇到她时，她问我
I first met her, she ask me if I had

1409
01:00:15,240 --> 01:00:17,370
是否已经将那无知改掉了
gotten all that foolishness out of my system.

1410
01:00:17,380 --> 01:00:19,310
我说：宝目，只剩你和棒球
I said, "baby, it's you and baseball,

1411
01:00:19,310 --> 01:00:21,210
对我来说是重要的，听到吗，博诺？
"all what count to me." You hear me, Bono?

1412
01:00:21,210 --> 01:00:24,010
而我也真的那样想，她说：哪样较重要？
And I meant it, too. She said, "which one come first?"

1413
01:00:24,020 --> 01:00:27,120
我说：当然是棒球
I said, "well, ain't no doubt it's baseball.

1414
01:00:27,120 --> 01:00:29,150
但要是你留下来和我白头到老
"But you stick and get old with me,

1415
01:00:29,150 --> 01:00:30,920
我们的爱会比对棒球的爱更长寿
"and we'll both outlive this baseball."

1416
01:00:30,920 --> 01:00:32,060
我说对了吗，罗斯？
Am I right, Rose?

1417
01:00:35,120 --> 01:00:35,690
那是真的
And it's true.

1418
01:00:35,700 --> 01:00:37,320
老兄，闭嘴吧，你才没有说过
Man, hush your mouth. You ain't say no such thing.

1419
01:00:37,330 --> 01:00:39,700
你当时说“宝贝你知道你永远都是最重要的”
Talkin' about, "baby, you know you'll always be number one with me."

1420
01:00:39,700 --> 01:00:42,330
那才是你所说的
That's what you was talking.

1421
01:00:42,330 --> 01:00:44,300
那就是为何我那么爱这个女人
That's why I love this woman.

1422
01:00:44,420 --> 01:00:45,670
罗斯总会提醒你
Rose will keep you straight.

1423
01:00:45,700 --> 01:00:47,200
如果你误入歧途，她总会提醒你
You get off the track, she'll straighten you up.

1424
01:00:47,200 --> 01:00:48,870
里昂，你快点去接邦妮
Lyons, you better get on up and get Bonnie.

1425
01:00:49,070 --> 01:00:50,110
她在等你呢
She waiting on you.

1426
01:00:50,440 --> 01:00:51,180
- 嘿，爸  - 什么？
- Hey, pop.  - Yeah?

1427
01:00:51,210 --> 01:00:54,540
你应该来看看我表演
You ought to come down to the grill, hear me play.

1428
01:00:54,840 --> 01:00:56,110
老兄，我才不去
Oh, man, I ain't goin' down there.

1429
01:00:56,110 --> 01:00:57,450
我太老了，不适合到俱乐部
I'm too old to be hanging out in them clubs.

1430
01:00:57,450 --> 01:01:01,020
你得很出色才能在[酒吧和]烤肉店演出
You got to be good to play down at the grill.

1431
01:01:01,020 --> 01:01:02,420
来吧，爸
Come on, pop.

1432
01:01:02,420 --> 01:01:03,950
我明天还得早起
I got to get up in the morning.

1433
01:01:03,960 --> 01:01:06,320
你不用待到很晚
Well, you ain't gotta stay long.

1434
01:01:07,290 --> 01:01:11,090
不了，我打算吃了晚餐就去睡
No, I'm gonna eat my supper and go to bed.

1435
01:01:12,130 --> 01:01:15,100
那我走了，下次见
Well, I got to go. I'll see you later.

1436
01:01:18,370 --> 01:01:20,970
你别在我的发薪日出现
Don't you come by my house on my payday!

1437
01:01:21,170 --> 01:01:23,270
还有下次来先打电话，让别人知道
And pick up the phone, let somebody know you coming,

1438
01:01:23,270 --> 01:01:25,310
也带上邦妮，你知道我很想见她
and bring Bonnie, you know I'm always glad to see her.

1439
01:01:25,310 --> 01:01:29,040
好的，罗斯，保重
I'll do that, Rose. You take care now.

1440
01:01:29,050 --> 01:01:30,410
- 下次见，爸  - 好吧
- See you, pop.   - All right.

1441
01:01:30,410 --> 01:01:32,480
再见，博诺先生
See you, Mr. Bono.

1442
01:01:32,480 --> 01:01:34,120
再见，加布叔叔
See you, Uncle Gabe!

1443
01:01:34,120 --> 01:01:35,750
里昂！万兽之王！
Lyons! King of the jungle!

1444
01:01:37,520 --> 01:01:38,450
晚餐好了吗，女人？
Supper ready, woman?

1445
01:01:38,650 --> 01:01:39,990
我们有点事要做
Me and you got some business to take care of.

1446
01:01:39,990 --> 01:01:42,220
- 我会让你爽翻天  - 特洛伊，我说过了
- I'mma tear it up, too.  - Troy, I done told you now!

1447
01:01:42,230 --> 01:01:44,190
天啊，女人，是博诺而已，他就像家人一样
Oh, hell, woman, it's Bono. Bono like family.

1448
01:01:44,200 --> 01:01:46,400
我已经认识这朋友…
I done know this nigger since...

1449
01:01:46,400 --> 01:01:49,100
- 我认识你多久了？ - 很久了
- How long have I known you?  - It's been a long time.

1450
01:01:49,100 --> 01:01:51,430
我自斯基还是小朋友的时候就认识这朋友[应为电影]
I done known this nigger since Skippy was a pup!

1451
01:01:51,440 --> 01:01:53,370
经历了不少日子
Me and him done been through some times!

1452
01:01:53,370 --> 01:01:55,200
你说对了
You sure are right about that.

1453
01:01:55,210 --> 01:01:57,270
我认识他甚至比认识你还长，罗斯
Hell, I known him longer than I known you, Rose,

1454
01:01:57,270 --> 01:01:59,210
至今我们还是好朋友
and we still standin' shoulder to shoulder.

1455
01:01:59,210 --> 01:02:02,510
夫复何求啊博诺
Look here, Bono, a man can't ask for no more than that.

1456
01:02:02,510 --> 01:02:04,080
我爱你，朋友
I love you, nigger.

1457
01:02:04,080 --> 01:02:06,080
天啊别来这套，我也爱你
Oh, hell! I love you, too.

1458
01:02:06,080 --> 01:02:09,150
但我得回去，你在这里能见你的女人
But I got to get home, see my woman. You got yours in hand.

1459
01:02:09,350 --> 01:02:11,050
我得回去才能见到她
I got to go get mine.

1460
01:02:12,790 --> 01:02:14,730
你为何这样做，爸？
What you do that for, pop?

1461
01:02:14,730 --> 01:02:16,760
科丽，什么事了？
What's the matter? Cory, what's the matter?

1462
01:02:16,760 --> 01:02:18,130
爸到学校跟泽尔曼教练说
Pop done went up to the school and told Coach Zellman

1463
01:02:18,130 --> 01:02:19,290
我不能继续打美式足球
I can't play football no more.

1464
01:02:19,300 --> 01:02:21,060
也不让我比赛和练习
Wouldn't even let me play the game.

1465
01:02:21,070 --> 01:02:22,430
他告诉教练叫球队负责人别来找他
Told him to tell the recruiter not to come.

1466
01:02:22,430 --> 01:02:24,370
- 特洛伊  - 你叫我做什么？
- Troy.  - What you Troying me for?

1467
01:02:24,370 --> 01:02:26,100
对，我的确做了，那小子知道原因
Yeah, I did it. And the boy knows why I did it.

1468
01:02:26,100 --> 01:02:28,100
你为何要这样对我？那是我唯一的机会啊！
Why you wanna do that to me? That was the one chance I had!

1469
01:02:28,110 --> 01:02:29,470
让科丽打美式足球又没什么问题，特洛伊
Ain't nothing wrong with Cory playing football, Troy.

1470
01:02:29,540 --> 01:02:30,440
那小子欺骗了我
The boy lied to me.

1471
01:02:30,470 --> 01:02:33,340
我跟那臭小子说过：你想继续打
I told the nigger, "you want to play football,

1472
01:02:33,410 --> 01:02:34,310
就得继续完成家务
"you keep up with your chores

1473
01:02:34,340 --> 01:02:37,350
继续在A&P工作，那就是条件
